<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="368" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="35.[132,775,332,383]" pageId="35" pageNumber="368">ETYMOLOGY. — Dedicated to Megan Zampa, granddaughter of one of the authors (B. Amati).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="368" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="35.[132,774,439,561]" box="[132,431,439,465]" pageId="35" pageNumber="368">
DESCRIPTION OF 
<typeStatus box="[320,431,444,463]" pageId="35" pageNumber="368">HOLOTYPE</typeStatus>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[132,774,439,561]" box="[132,413,470,497]" pageId="35" pageNumber="368">
<emphasis box="[132,413,470,497]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="368">
Shell (
<figureCitation box="[196,271,470,497]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="33.[132,143,1793,1811]" captionTargetBox="[132,1455,216,1747]" captionTargetId="figure-70@33.[132,1455,216,1747]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIG. 18. — Benthonellania megan n. sp.: A-E, holotype,height 2.7 mm, width 1.6 mm Marquesas:MUSORSTOM 9 Stn DR1247 1150-1250 m 10°34’S,138°42’W, type locality, MNHN-IM-2000-37695; F-H, paratype, height 2.7 mm, width 1.6 mm, type locality, MNHN-IM-2000-37696; I-K, paratype, height 2.5 mm, width 1.475 mm, type locality, MNHN-IM-2000-37696. Scale bar: D, E, 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6794884" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6794884/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="368">Figs 18</figureCitation>
A-C; 19F-H)
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[132,774,439,561]" pageId="35" pageNumber="368">
Small for the genus, height 
<quantity box="[428,517,502,529]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="35" pageNumber="368" unit="mm" value="2.7">2.7 mm</quantity>
, width 
<quantity box="[598,687,502,529]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="35" pageNumber="368" unit="mm" value="1.6">1.6 mm</quantity>
, height/ width ratio 1.687, pretty solid, ovate-conical.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[131,777,598,847]" box="[132,493,598,624]" pageId="35" pageNumber="368">
<emphasis box="[132,493,598,624]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="368">
Protoconch (
<figureCitation box="[259,388,598,624]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="33.[132,143,1793,1811]" captionTargetBox="[132,1455,216,1747]" captionTargetId="figure-70@33.[132,1455,216,1747]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIG. 18. — Benthonellania megan n. sp.: A-E, holotype,height 2.7 mm, width 1.6 mm Marquesas:MUSORSTOM 9 Stn DR1247 1150-1250 m 10°34’S,138°42’W, type locality, MNHN-IM-2000-37695; F-H, paratype, height 2.7 mm, width 1.6 mm, type locality, MNHN-IM-2000-37696; I-K, paratype, height 2.5 mm, width 1.475 mm, type locality, MNHN-IM-2000-37696. Scale bar: D, E, 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6794884" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6794884/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="368">Figs 18D, E</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation box="[401,484,598,624]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="34.[132,143,1675,1693]" captionTargetBox="[132,1453,216,1629]" captionTargetId="figure-168@34.[132,1453,216,1629]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIG. 19. — Benthonellania spp. (SEM): A-E, Benthonellania tarava n. sp., holotype, Tarava Seamounts, height 3.5 mm, MNHN-IM-2000-37687: shell (A); detail of the protoconch microsculture (B-D); detail of the teleoconch axial sculture (E); F-H, Benthonellania megan n. sp., holotype, Marquesas, height 2.7 mm, MNHN- IM-2000-37695: shell (F); detail of the protoconch microsculture (G, H). Scale bars: B, E, G, H, 100 μm; C, 20 μm; D, 50 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6794886" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6794886/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="368">19G, H</figureCitation>
)
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[131,777,598,847]" pageId="35" pageNumber="368">
Multispiral, acute of 2.5 whorls, height 
<quantity box="[574,679,630,656]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="35" pageNumber="368" unit="mm" value="0.4">0.40 mm</quantity>
, nucleus diameter 
<quantity box="[239,359,661,688]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" pageId="35" pageNumber="368" unit="mm" value="0.095">0.095 mm</quantity>
, first half whorl diameter 
<quantity box="[652,772,662,688]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.62" pageId="35" pageNumber="368" unit="mm" value="0.162">0.162 mm</quantity>
, maximum diameter 
<quantity box="[355,473,694,720]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.37" pageId="35" pageNumber="368" unit="mm" value="0.437">0.437 mm</quantity>
; (protoconch I in poor condition), protoconch II with two fine spiral keels, the lower larger, a fine cordlet of microtubercles in the subsutural area. Microtubercles spread over the entire surface (
<figureCitation box="[624,759,789,815]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="34.[132,143,1675,1693]" captionTargetBox="[132,1453,216,1629]" captionTargetId="figure-168@34.[132,1453,216,1629]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIG. 19. — Benthonellania spp. (SEM): A-E, Benthonellania tarava n. sp., holotype, Tarava Seamounts, height 3.5 mm, MNHN-IM-2000-37687: shell (A); detail of the protoconch microsculture (B-D); detail of the teleoconch axial sculture (E); F-H, Benthonellania megan n. sp., holotype, Marquesas, height 2.7 mm, MNHN- IM-2000-37695: shell (F); detail of the protoconch microsculture (G, H). Scale bars: B, E, G, H, 100 μm; C, 20 μm; D, 50 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6794886" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6794886/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="368">Fig. 19G, H</figureCitation>
). Protoconch-teleoconch boundary barely visible, sinuous.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[132,777,885,1262]" box="[132,241,885,911]" pageId="35" pageNumber="368">
<emphasis box="[132,241,885,911]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="368">Teleoconch</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[132,777,885,1262]" pageId="35" pageNumber="368">
Of 
<emphasis box="[175,192,918,943]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="368">c.</emphasis>
3.5 convex whorls, suture canaliculate, crowned by small tubercles at tips of axial ribs. Height last whorl 
<quantity box="[134,238,980,1007]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" pageId="35" pageNumber="368" unit="mm" value="1.75">1.75 mm</quantity>
, height/height last whorl ratio 1.542. Axial sculpture of 16 curved, slightly opisthocline ribs on last whorl, slightly narrower than interspaces, abruptly interrupted on the suture line. Spiral sculpture of 3 very weak fine cordlets on the base. Microsculpture of only growth striae (
<figureCitation box="[140,250,1140,1166]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="34.[132,143,1675,1693]" captionTargetBox="[132,1453,216,1629]" captionTargetId="figure-168@34.[132,1453,216,1629]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIG. 19. — Benthonellania spp. (SEM): A-E, Benthonellania tarava n. sp., holotype, Tarava Seamounts, height 3.5 mm, MNHN-IM-2000-37687: shell (A); detail of the protoconch microsculture (B-D); detail of the teleoconch axial sculture (E); F-H, Benthonellania megan n. sp., holotype, Marquesas, height 2.7 mm, MNHN- IM-2000-37695: shell (F); detail of the protoconch microsculture (G, H). Scale bars: B, E, G, H, 100 μm; C, 20 μm; D, 50 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6794886" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6794886/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="368">Fig. 19H</figureCitation>
). Umbilical chink absent. Aperture pyriform, large, height 
<quantity box="[281,373,1172,1198]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="35" pageNumber="368" unit="mm" value="1.1">1.1 mm</quantity>
, height/height aperture ratio 2.454, peristome continuous, varix absent (outer lip broken). Columella arcuate, simple.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[132,776,1299,1358]" box="[132,203,1299,1325]" pageId="35" pageNumber="368">
<emphasis box="[132,203,1299,1325]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="368">Colour</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[132,776,1299,1358]" box="[132,776,1331,1358]" pageId="35" pageNumber="368">Coloration of teleoconch translucent white, protoconch orange.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[132,393,1395,1453]" box="[132,393,1395,1421]" pageId="35" pageNumber="368">
<emphasis box="[132,393,1395,1421]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="368">Operculum and soft parts</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[132,393,1395,1453]" box="[132,249,1427,1453]" pageId="35" pageNumber="368">Unknown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[132,748,1491,1549]" box="[132,262,1491,1517]" pageId="35" pageNumber="368">VARIABILITY</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[132,748,1491,1549]" box="[132,748,1523,1549]" pageId="35" pageNumber="368">
Species not very variable (See 
<tableCitation box="[456,536,1523,1549]" captionStart="TABLE" captionStartId="7.[126,137,482,504]" captionText="TABLE 1. — Measurements of teleoconch and protoconch of the studied species in mm,with minimum-maximum range and mean [standard deviation in square parentheses]. Sample size in parentheses with the species name. Symbols: +, present;–, absent;M, multispiral;P, paucispiral." pageId="35" pageNumber="368">Table 1</tableCitation>
and 
<figureCitation box="[591,734,1523,1549]" captionStart="APPENDIX" captionStartId="55.[132,144,219,237]" captionText="APPENDIX 11. — Measurements of teleoconch and protoconch of Benthonellania megan n. sp. in mm, with range, mean and standard deviation: 1, holotype, Marquesas, Fatu Hiva, 1150-1250 m depth; 2, paratype, Marquesas: Fatu Hiva, 1150-1250 m depth; 3-5, paratypes Marquesas, Fatu Hiva, 1150-1250 m depth; 6, Australes, Rimatara, 1200-1226 m depth." pageId="35" pageNumber="368">Appendix 11</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="368" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="35.[130,777,1587,2028]" box="[132,232,1587,1613]" pageId="35" pageNumber="368">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[130,777,1587,2028]" pageId="35" pageNumber="368">All the examined specimens have a broken peristome (presence/absence of lip thickening not observable).</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[130,777,1587,2028]" pageId="35" pageNumber="368">
<taxonomicName authority="Amati &amp; Giulio &amp; Oliverio, 2022" authorityName="Amati &amp; Giulio &amp; Oliverio" authorityYear="2022" box="[155,250,1683,1708]" class="Gastropoda" family="Rissoidae" genus="Benthonellania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="35" pageNumber="368" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="tarava" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[155,250,1683,1708]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="368">B. tarava</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[255,313,1683,1709]" pageId="35" pageNumber="368" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Amati &amp; Giulio &amp; Oliverio, 2022" authorityName="Amati &amp; Giulio &amp; Oliverio" authorityYear="2022" box="[449,544,1683,1708]" class="Gastropoda" family="Rissoidae" genus="Benthonellania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="35" pageNumber="368" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="megan" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[449,544,1683,1708]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="368">B. megan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[550,608,1683,1709]" pageId="35" pageNumber="368" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in its larger size height 
<quantity box="[208,368,1714,1741]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.335" metricValueMax="3.75" metricValueMin="2.92" pageId="35" pageNumber="368" unit="mm" value="3.335" valueMax="3.75" valueMin="2.92">2.92-3.75 mm</quantity>
vs heigh 
<quantity box="[475,635,1714,1741]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.55" metricValueMax="2.7" metricValueMin="2.4" pageId="35" pageNumber="368" unit="mm" value="2.55" valueMax="2.7" valueMin="2.4">2.40-2.70 mm</quantity>
in 
<taxonomicName authority="Amati &amp; Giulio &amp; Oliverio, 2022" authorityName="Amati &amp; Giulio &amp; Oliverio" authorityYear="2022" box="[674,773,1715,1740]" class="Gastropoda" family="Rissoidae" genus="Benthonellania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="35" pageNumber="368" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="megan" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[674,773,1715,1740]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="368">B. megan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[132,196,1746,1772]" pageId="35" pageNumber="368" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, higher height/width ratio 
<geoCoordinate box="[502,567,1746,1773]" degrees="1.859" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="35" pageNumber="368" precision="55" value="1.859">1.859</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate box="[567,639,1746,1773]" degrees="1.807" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="35" pageNumber="368" precision="55" value="-1.807">-1.807</geoCoordinate>
vs 
<quantity box="[679,774,1746,1772]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.22148" pageId="35" pageNumber="368" unit="in" value="1.662">1.662 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Amati &amp; Giulio &amp; Oliverio" authorityYear="2022" box="[134,228,1779,1804]" class="Gastropoda" family="Rissoidae" genus="Benthonellania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="35" pageNumber="368" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="megan">
<emphasis box="[134,228,1779,1804]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="368">B. megan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; more whorls 4-4.65 vs 
<quantity box="[478,610,1778,1805]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.509" metricValueMax="8.89" metricValueMin="8.128" pageId="35" pageNumber="368" unit="in" value="3.35" valueMax="3.5" valueMin="3.2">3.20-3.50 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName authority="Amati &amp; Giulio &amp; Oliverio, 2022" authorityName="Amati &amp; Giulio &amp; Oliverio" authorityYear="2022" box="[614,708,1779,1804]" class="Gastropoda" family="Rissoidae" genus="Benthonellania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="35" pageNumber="368" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="megan" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[614,708,1779,1804]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="368">B. megan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[714,772,1778,1804]" pageId="35" pageNumber="368" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, less numerous axial ribs on the last whorl 11-14 (mean 12.6) vs 14-19 (mean 16.5) in 
<taxonomicName authority="Amati &amp; Giulio &amp; Oliverio, 2022" authorityName="Amati &amp; Giulio &amp; Oliverio" authorityYear="2022" box="[391,487,1842,1867]" class="Gastropoda" family="Rissoidae" genus="Benthonellania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="35" pageNumber="368" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="megan" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[391,487,1842,1867]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="368">B. megan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[492,551,1842,1868]" pageId="35" pageNumber="368" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, and its more slender protoconch with two fine spiral cordlets, with a large smooth median area, and a fine spiral cordlet below the abapical cordlets vs two fine spiral cordlets, the lower larger, a fine cordlet of microtubercles in the subsutural area and microtubercles over the entire surface in 
<taxonomicName authority="Amati &amp; Giulio &amp; Oliverio, 2022" authorityName="Amati &amp; Giulio &amp; Oliverio" authorityYear="2022" box="[405,502,2002,2027]" class="Gastropoda" family="Rissoidae" genus="Benthonellania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="35" pageNumber="368" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="megan" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[405,502,2002,2027]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="368">B. megan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[510,568,2002,2028]" pageId="35" pageNumber="368" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
